HESPER The Health Services and Performance Research laboratory


   The Health Services and Performance Research (HESPER) laboratory
   is a public

   health laboratory composed of an interdisciplinary research team that
   is aimed at :
     * advancing the knowledge on health services, healthcare
       services, and the

             patient clinical pathway
     * study their performances in terms of : quality, safety, efficiency,
       accessibility


          [1okkk.png]              [2okkk.png]

   Axis 1 : The performance of health care services

   To measure and improve healthcare services safety and performance
     * Analysis of individual and collective determinants of performance
     * Development and scientific evaluation of performance indicators
     * Research methods to measure the impact of actions

   Axis 2 : the patient / the user

   To measure and improve safety and performance of the patient’s pathway
     * Determinants of pathways breaks
     * Development and evaluation of patient engagement / empowerment
       methods
     * development and evaluation support systems to the referral (system
       “navigation”)










